Emanate builds solutions that continuously monitor the operation and productivity of key clinical assets at healthcare facilities.  

Emanate's PowerPath Temp solution ELIMINATES expensive loss of pharmaceutical inventory caused by spoilage.    Consider this -- refrigerators typically fail once every 10 years -- so a hospital with 50 pharmacy refrigerators experiences an average of *5* failure events per year.   A slow response to just one of these failure events results in losses approaching a hundred thousand dollars.   Emanate's solution eliminates the need for emergency response to refrigerator failure by providing advanced warning before failure even occurs!   How does it work?  By monitoring both temp and AC power of the refrigeration devices and applying AI, the system detects anomalies such as a laboring compressors and failing defrosters *before* they cause a failure.

Emanate's next generation UCLS (Utilization, Condition, and Location System) ELIMINATES expensive costs associated with over-inventory and service of medical equipment.   Studies have shown that a typical hospital has 25% over-inventory of medical equipment.  As an example, for a 200 bed hospital this extra inventory results in $750K annually in unnecessary Capex and Opex.  Why do hospitals have too much equipment?   Because they have no way to measure actual equipment utilization - and so must guess at optimal inventory levels.  Emanate has created a unique solution that uses sensors and AI Machine Learning to MEASURE the utilization of assets such as pumps monitors, and imaging devices.  This measured utilization feeds data-driven analysis of optimal inventory levels – “How much equipment do we really need, and where?”   Further savings are achieved by optimizing equipment service to be usage-based and condition-based rather than time-based.   Patient safety is also enhanced by detecting field faults requiring service - such as power surges, drops, and failing mechanical components.

Celik has innovated the exchange of digital business cards within mobile phones, allowing subscribers to grow their mobile phonebooks and enrich their social networks. He pioneered an interactive messaging service which is triggered upon a missed call. Celik has transformed Mobile Marketing by deepening Mobile Operators’ and Brands’ relationship with their subscribers through an interactive and meaningful channel. Çelik raised over $26 million in funding for OnePIN from four Venture Capital firms: Stage 1 
Ventures, QKA, L.P., Egan Managed Capital and Greycroft Partners.

Prior to founding OnePIN, Çelik served as President and CEO of the North American division of Koc Group, a $40 billion Fortune Global 500 .

Çelik holds a master’s degree in business administration with high distinction from the Babson College Graduate School of Business, a master’s degree in mechanical engineering from Boston University and a bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering from the Middle East Technical University (METU) College of Engineering.

Çelik is the recipient of the Babson College W.F. Glavin Center Global Entrepreneur Award.
Çelik holds 60+ global patents related to OnePIN technologies. Çelik is also the main inventor on a number of patents currently in the pending stage both nationally and internationally.

MatSing’s patented and vetted lens technology enables them to be at the forefront of the antenna industry.  Starting in 2005 with an expertise in metamaterials, they used that knowledge to design and create the world’s first large, lightweight, multi-beam RF lenses.  Their unique technology has brought a new age of high-performance and high-capacity antennas to the telecommunications industry.
MatSing provides a range of antennas for all applications (Macro, Events, and Venues) allowing customers to select the correct antenna type based on the number of cell site locations and required capacity.  Each antenna provides multiple independent sectors covering multiple bands, allowing users to have the highest capacity from the fewest locations—up to 48 independent sectors from a single antenna.
The new and unique design of the MatSing antennas provides the best radio frequency signal control in the industry, giving users exceptional RF performance at much lower power.  MatSing lens technology is the perfect fit for 4G, LTE, and 5G, and it is seen as the most cost-effective network densification tool in the industry.

We are an unbiased telecommunications agency.   Just like an independent insurance agency can bring you quotations and coverages from multiple insurance carriers, Top Speed Data can find the best solution for your company’s situation.

We don’t work for any one carrier.  We represent over 40 different telecommunications providers so we can find the right solution for your needs.

The process is simple.

Our experienced network design consultant will sit down with you to get an understanding of the way you do business.  We seek to understand where you are and where you are headed.  We then perform a complimentary assessment of your voice, data, and wireless services.   Then we present you with several options and explain each one.

If you like what you see, we can then submit and process all the orders with the carriers and provide you with complete telecom project management.  And we do not charge you a dime.  The carriers compensate us from the sales and direct marketing costs that are already built into the pricing that they would charge you if you were to buy from them direct. 

We specialize in reducing your telecom costs and increasing your network performance at the same time.  We act as your advocate throughout the design, implementation, and billing processes.   We work for you!!

Headquartered in Washington, DC, CCA advocates on behalf of members’ interests and works to educate policymakers on the key issues that impact members’ ability to compete, survive, and thrive. Advocating before the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), the White House and Congress, CCA works to ensure that our members’ voices and views are heard not only by policymakers but also by the media, third parties and throughout the entire wireless industry.

There are hundreds of companies that offer recruiting services offering high quality candidates. The question is, do they screen and scrutinize the candidates prior to engaging the client? More than 80% of the companies merely pass on the resumes and let the client do all the hard work.

The age old question of  “I’m moving to the cloud, but what do  we do about these analog POTS lines?” is finally solved . . . and the answer is literally EPIK. 
 
EPIK is the creator and distributor of the innovative EPIK (Ethernet-POTS-Integration-Kit), a unique device that addresses specific challenges that all businesses share . . . 
•	Finding an affordable & reliable solution to replace outdated, costly, and “endangered” copper POTS lines 
•	Identifying a robust and dependable, high-speed Internet solution for back-up/failover and business continuity
•	Assuring “always up” telecom and Internet environment . . . even WHEN the internet is down, and /or the power is out. 
 
The combination of Ethernet, 4G, and soft-switch technology into an easy to deploy and affordable appliance is transforming the way customers connect (and stay connected) The EPIK appliance delivers POT’s replacement, network resiliency, disaster avoidance, and even solves the single-threaded connectivity problem.  
 
EPIK is the ultimate companion product that fills in the missing pieces while also delivering immediate savings and improved performance.  At EPIK, we like to say that we “COMPLETE” rather than “COMPETE”.
 
We are dedicated, not only to delivering a great product, but also to building a world class company that provides customers with unmatched service levels delivered by the very best Channel Partners.
